President Biden is set to meet with Chancellor Olaf Scholz of Germany on February 7, 2022, at the White House. The purpose of the meeting is to strengthen the longstanding relationship between the United States and Germany. The leaders will discuss their shared commitment to diplomacy and efforts to prevent further aggression from Russia towards Ukraine. Additionally, they will address the importance of close cooperation in tackling common challenges such as ending the COVID-19 pandemic, addressing climate change, and promoting economic prosperity and international security based on democratic values.